"title": "5189: teeth",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5189",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture often uses teeth symbolically, to refer to the power of individuals or to human rage (as in the “gnashing of teeth”).</p>\n<h2>Teeth in a literal sense</h2>\n<h3>In eating</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:33\">NUM 11:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:5\">DAN 7:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:7\">DAN 7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:19\">DAN 7:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:7\">ZEC 9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:8\">REV 9:8</a></p>\n<h3>As an object of beauty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:2\">SNG 4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:12\">GEN 49:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song6:6\">SNG 6:6</a></p>\n<h3>As an object of fear</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:14\">JOB 41:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:24\">DEU 32:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:16\">JOB 20:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:6\">JOL 1:6</a></p>\n<h2>Teeth used symbolically</h2>\n<h3>To represent offensive weapons</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:4\">PSA 57:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:14\">PRO 30:14</a></p>\n<h3>To symbolise military power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:15\">ISA 41:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:6\">JOL 1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:3\">AMO 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:12\">HAB 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>God rescues his people from the teeth of their enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps124:6\">PSA 124:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:10\">JOB 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:20-Dan6:21\">DAN 6:20–6:21</a></p>\n<h3>Breaking the teeth of the wicked ends their power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps3:7\">PSA 3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:17\">JOB 29:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps58:6\">PSA 58:6</a> <em>Enemies are often described as dangerous animals.</em></p>\n<h2>Gnashing of teeth</h2>\n<h3>In rage</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:54\">ACT 7:54</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job16:9\">JOB 16:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:16\">PSA 35:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:12\">PSA 37:12</a></p>\n<h3>In frustration</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps112:10\">PSA 112:10</a></p>\n<h3>In anguish</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:12\">MAT 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:42\">MAT 13:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:50\">MAT 13:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:13\">MAT 22:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:51\">MAT 24:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:30\">MAT 25:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:28\">LUK 13:28</a></p>\n<h3>In gloating</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:16\">LAM 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>Under demonic influence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:18\">MRK 9:18</a></p>\n<h2>Proverbial sayings about teeth</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:20\">JOB 19:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:26\">PRO 10:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:29-Jer31:30\">JER 31:29–31:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:2\">EZK 18:2</a></p>",
